Offcn Education suspected of having a funding chain break
In recent years, the number of people taking the civil service exam has been rising steadily. As China's largest civil service exam training institution, Offcn Education has also made a lot of money. It has also launched the "agreement class" model, which is the so-called refund if you don't pass.
However, recently many students who signed the agreement found that they couldn't get a refund if they didn't pass the exam. After a long period of rights protection
Offcn recently came up with an installment payment, with a refund in ten installments, and everyone finally couldn't help but go offline to argue.
